					<dc:identifier>http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2006/965/regulation/2/2025-04-07</dc:identifier><dc:title>The Child Benefit (Rates) Regulations 2006</dc:title><dc:type>text</dc:type><dc:format>text/xml</dc:format><dc:language>en</dc:language><dc:publisher>Statute Law Database</dc:publisher><dc:subject scheme="SIheading">SOCIAL SECURITY</dc:subject><dc:modified>2025-05-14</dc:modified><dc:contributor>Expert Participation</dc:contributor><dct:valid>2025-04-07</dct:valid>
					<dc:description>These Regulations replace the Child Benefit and Social Security (Fixing and Adjustment of Rates) Regulations 1976 and the Child Benefit and Social Security (Fixing and Adjustment of Rates) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1976 with a single instrument covering the whole of the United Kingdom.</dc:description>
